{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d9cba46a-bf21-4397-877e-3b90b6284569","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. When you use `dotnet run`, the test host stays alive, watches for file changes, and re-runs affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the classic VSTest adapter and doesn't support the hot reload workflow — it runs tests once and exits.\n\nSo:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run\n```\n\nThis will start the test host in hot-reload mode, and as you edit your source/test files, tests will automatically re-execute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7f6dcd18-e671-4ff9-97a9-9882b80a1681","outputTokens":149,"requestId":"341B:3675E8:B78703:D76A21:69F4056C"},"id":"63dff396-64dc-461c-bda4-9e3f3f44538c","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:44:19.025Z","parentId":"fedb6c2a-b2d7-4904-84be-4f712c4fa2c0"}
